Activity: A7 - Discover cryptography used in modern networks

Objective
The goal of this activity was to investigate and identify cryptographic methods used in modern networks to protect data transmission

Method
I examined the security settings of my home WiFi network and network connected applications. I looked at the encryption protocols used and noted which protocols protect data as it travels across the network. I also checked VPN settings to see how they encrypt my connection when online.

Findings
The investigation revealed the following cryptographic implementations:
1. Wifi encryption - protects wireless communication between devices and the router
2. VPN encryption - secures data traffic between my device and external servers
3. HTTPS connections - websites use Transport Layer Security to encrypt data exchanged with my browser

Security Principle
These cryptographic implementations support confidentiality by ensuring data cannot be read by unauthorised parties, integrity by preventing tampering, and availability by maintaing secure connections for users.

Reflection
This activity helped me understand how modern networks rely on cryptography to secure data in transit. it demonstrated the importance of using up-to-date encryption standards like WPA3 and TLS to protect personal and sensitive information
